[Matthew 24:3](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">mat 24:3</span></span>

Tell us

The beginning of the Olivet Discourse.

Comparing Matthew 24 with ([Luk
21:20-24](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#020).md) answers the threefold
question. The order is as follows: "when shall these things be?" -- that
is, destruction of the temple and city. Answer: ([Luk
21:20-24](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#020).md).

Second and third questions: "And what shall be the sign of thy coming,
and of the end of the age?" Answer: ([Mat
24:4-33](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#004).md).

Verses 4 to 14 ([Mat 24:4-14](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#004).md) have a
double interpretation: They give

\(1\) the character of the age -- wars, international conflicts,
famines, pestilences, persecutions, and false Christs. Compare ([Dan
9:26](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#026).md).

This is not the description of a converted world.

\(2\) But the same answer ([Mat
24:4-14](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#004).md) applies in a specific way to
the end of the age, namely, Daniel's seventieth week. ([Dan
9:24-27](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#024).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Dan 9:24](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#024).md).

All that has characterized the age gathers into awful intensity at the
end. Verse 14 ([Mat 24:14](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#014).md) has
specific reference to the proclamation of the good news that the kingdom
is again "at hand" by the Jewish remnant ([Isa
1:9](../../../bib/kjv/isa001.htm#009).md); ([Rev
14:6](../../../bib/kjv/rev014.htm#006).md); ([Rev
14:7](../../../bib/kjv/rev014.htm#007).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Rom 11:5](../../../bib/kjv/rom011.htm#005).md).

Verse 15 ([Mat 24:15](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#015).md) gives the sign
of the abomination,

(See Scofield) - ([Dan 9:27](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#027).md),

the "man of sin," or "Beast". ([Th2
2:3-8](../../../bib/kjv/th2002.htm#003).md); ([Dan
9:27](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#027).md); ([Dan
12:11](../../../bib/kjv/dan012.htm#011).md); ([Rev
13:4-7](../../../bib/kjv/rev013.htm#004).md).

This introduces the great tribulation ([Psa
2:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa002.htm#005).md).

(See Scofield) - ([Rev 7:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev007.htm#014).md),

which runs its awful course of three and a half years, culminating in
the battle of

(See Scofield) - ([Rev 19:19](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#019).md),

at which time Christ becomes the smiting Stone of ([Dan
2:34](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#034).md).

The detail of this period ([Mat
24:15-28](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#015).md) is:

\(1\) The abomination in the holy place ([Mat
24:15](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#015).md);

\(2\) the warning ([Mat 24:16-20](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#016).md) to
believing Jews who will then be in Jerusalem;

\(3\) the great tribulation, with renewed warning as to false Christs
([Mat 24:21-26](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#021).md);

\(4\) the sudden smiting of the Gentile world-power ([Mat
24:27](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#027).md); ([Mat
24:28](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#028).md);

\(5\) the glorious appearing of the Lord, visible to all nations, and
the regathering of Israel ([Mat
24:29-31](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#029).md);

\(6\) the sign of the fig-tree ([Mat
24:32](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#032).md); ([Mat
24:33](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#033).md);

\(7\) warnings, applicable to this present age over which these events
are ever impending ([Mat 24:34-51](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#034).md).
([Plm 4:5](../../../bib/kjv/plm004.htm#005).md).

Careful study of Daniel 2, 7, 9 and Revelation 13 will make the
interpretation clear.

See, also, "Remnant" ([Isa 1:9](../../../bib/kjv/isa001.htm#009).md); ([Rom
11:5](../../../bib/kjv/rom011.htm#005).md).

